import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'])
    plt.xlabel('US Gross')
    plt.ylabel('Worldwide Gross')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Production_Budget'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Production_Budget'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Production_Budget'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Production_Budget'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Production Budget')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Production_Budget?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,6))
    ax.boxplot([data['Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating'], data['IMDB_Rating']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Rotten Tomatoes Rating', 'IMDB Rating'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Rating')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Rotten_Tomatoes_Rating and IMDB_Rating?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Running_Time_min'])
    plt.hist(data['Running_Time_min'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Running_Time_min'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Running_Time_min'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (min)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
    ax = data['MPAA_Rating'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    ax.set_xlabel('MPAA Rating')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating?')
    for i in ax.patches:
        ax.text(i.get_x()+0.2, i.get_height()+1, str(i.get_height()), fontsize=10, color='black')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
